  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2902734622" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2902734622" />
    <a title="Gabi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/84001290-gabi"><img alt="Gabi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1608919962p2/84001290.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2902734622?book_show_action=true">Jul 21, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gabi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gabi" href="/user/show/84001290-gabi">Gabi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84001290-gabi?shelf=locus_winners">locus_winners</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84001290-gabi?shelf=hugo_nominees">hugo_nominees</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/84001290-gabi?shelf=nebula_winners">nebula_winners</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2902734622" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1924087543532423284">4.5 stars - cause I&apos;m still (or even more so) grossed out by Severian&apos;s take on women. What a horrible character!<br/><br/><b>There is no magic. There is only knowledge, more or less hidden.</b><br/><br/>This sentence from the last chapter summarizes my take on the novels pretty well. Meanwhile I&apos;m convinced that I&apos;m not reading a Fantasy novel, but a cleverly staged SF novel. So while reading I try to put together all the bits and pieces of weird information in context of aliens, bioengineering, time travel machines and </span>
  <span id="freeText1924087543532423284" style="display:none">4.5 stars - cause I'm still (or even more so) grossed out by Severian's take on women. What a horrible character!<br /><br /><b>There is no magic. There is only knowledge, more or less hidden.</b><br /><br />This sentence from the last chapter summarizes my take on the novels pretty well. Meanwhile I'm convinced that I'm not reading a Fantasy novel, but a cleverly staged SF novel. So while reading I try to put together all the bits and pieces of weird information in context of aliens, bioengineering, time travel machines and such. I have no idea where this all leads, but it is a hell lot of fun for readers who love guessing and solving puzzles.<br /><br />Severian's emotional state seems even more perturbed than in the first novel. His spontaneous affidavits of loyalty and love seem to have no grounding in any facts, but feel like whims of the moment. Yet it is clear that he himself dearly believes everything he feels and remembers to be true. It is the reader's part to try to get some sense and order into his tale. And Gene Wolfe doesn't make this easy for us - no way.<br /><br />We get more hints about the nature of Urth and its society and Severian's possible role in past and future, but all in all we are left with even more questions at the end of the second book.<br /><br />Which means: Forget my meticulously planned reading schedule with Buddy Reads and on to the third book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1924087543532423284" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


