<div id="review_3589584383" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3589584383" />
    <a title="Dawn C" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14948447-dawn-c"><img alt="Dawn C" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1535435406p2/14948447.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3589584383?book_show_action=true">Nov 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dawn C" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dawn C" href="/user/show/14948447-dawn-c">Dawn C</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14948447-dawn-c?shelf=media-audible">media-audible</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3589584383" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17643012032884190427">Okay, hear me out. I absolutely <i>adore</i> the lore, the mythology and the writing of this series, which makes it all the more painful that I’m finding myself growing annoyed with our man Severian. Rarely has a character lacked a personality as much as he does. He might as well be completely blank. What’s this man passionate about? What does he want, what does he fight for, what makes him go? Two books in and I have no idea who he is. I know he’s a torturer and an executioner, though he doesn’t seem </span>
  <span id="freeText17643012032884190427" style="display:none">Okay, hear me out. I absolutely <i>adore</i> the lore, the mythology and the writing of this series, which makes it all the more painful that I’m finding myself growing annoyed with our man Severian. Rarely has a character lacked a personality as much as he does. He might as well be completely blank. What’s this man passionate about? What does he want, what does he fight for, what makes him go? Two books in and I have no idea who he is. I know he’s a torturer and an executioner, though he doesn’t seem to really feel one way or the other about any of that, either. I know he likes women, all of them, and believes himself somewhat intellectual, I guess, the way he “philosophizes” over love and lust. These women are for some unfathomable reason also attracted to him, because an wishy-washy killer is apparently very attractive. I just have absolutely no idea what anyone sees in him. He must be <i>really</i> well-endowed down there.<br /><br />But I'm enjoying the story and the writing, so I will definitely continute the saga.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17643012032884190427" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


